#
# 3.5 Edition D&D Random Dragon Stats
#
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# To call this table from another one:
#    [Dragon Stats.CheckVariableStatus(%DragonType%,%DragonAge%,
#                                      %Bonus0Level%,,%Ally4%,%AllyCount4%)]
#
#             (Default Value)
#    DragonType:  (13) Choose a Dragon Type
#                      1=Black, 2=Blue, 3=Green, 4=Red, 5=White, 6=Brass,
#                      7=Bronze, 8=Copper, 9=Gold, 10=Silver, 
#                      11=Random Chromatic, 12=Random Metallic, 13=Random Any
#    DragonAge:   (13) 1=Wyrmling, 2=Very Young, 3=Young, 4=Juvenile,
#                      5=Young Adult, 6=Adult, 7=Mature Adult, 8=Old,
#                      9=Very Old, 10=Ancient, 11=Wyrm, 12=Great Wyrm, 
#                      13=Random
#    Bonus0Level: (2)  1= Yes, add 0-Level bonus spells.
#                      2= No 0-Level bonus spells.
#    Instructions:(1)  1= Shows instructions (if called from .Start)
#                      2= To activate the table (if called from .Start)
#    Ally4:       (0)  DO NOT MODIFY (only to link with Monster Stats.tab)
#    AllyCount4:  (0)  DO NOT MODIFY (only to link with Monster Stats.tab)
#
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Modified by Valminder, Dec 2005.
#    Adapted for TSv5.
#    Added a lot of modifications.
#       Example: changed some functions.
#                Dragon can't have Cleave if no Power Attack feat.
#    Removed [OrgDescription] subtable and added link to 
#       [Monster Stats.OrganizationDescription]
#    Will be called from "Monster Stats.tab"
#
# Modified by Larry Cormier, Jan 2006.
#    Revised Parameter Prompts so they will not be 'Cut-off' due to
#       prompt length limitations in TableSmith v4.5
#    Revised NumberAppearing table to eliminate redundant'Dragon Families'
#       being generated for offspring
#    Revised some display code for Aesthetic and Grammatical reasons
#
# Modified by Larry Cormier, Feb 2006.
#    Added Bold Font style and an Attribute identifier for ease of use,
#       and consistant integration with Monster Stats.tab
# Modified by Valminder, Feb 2006.
#    The feats and skills were not displayed in alphabetical order due to
#    too many spaces here and there. Everything is now fixed.
#

