:Instructions
1,This table generates Stats for 3.5 Edition D&D Dragons.<br><br>
_ Use the Parameter Button located in the Upper Left-hand corner of the screen to Input a MonsterID to get started.<br><br>
_To call this table from another one, you need to feed it the parameters in the order listed below:<br>
_<font color=green>Dragon Stats.CheckVariableStatus(DragonType,DragonAge,Bonus0Level,Instructions,Ally4,AllyCount4)</font><br><br>
_<b>Example:</b> Gold Dragon, Great Wyrm, without 0-Level bonus spells.<br>
_<font color=green>Dragon Stats.CheckVariableStatus(9,12,2)</font> (You do not need the last 3 parameters)<br><br>
_<b>DragonType:</b><font color=darkred> (Default=13)</font> 1=Black, 2=Blue, 3=Green, 4=Red, 5=White, 6=Brass,
_ 7=Bronze, 8=Copper, 9=Gold, 10=Silver, 11=Random Chromatic, 12=Random Metallic, 13=Random Any<br>
_<b>DragonAge:</b> <font color=darkred>(Default=13)</font> 1=Wyrmling, 2=Very Young, 3=Young, 4=Juvenile, 5=Young Adult,
_ 6=Adult, 7=Mature Adult, 8=Old, 9=Very Old, 10=Ancient, 11=Wyrm, 12=Great Wyrm, 13=Random<br>
_<b>Bonus0Level:</b> <font color=darkred>(Default=2)</font>  1= Yes, add 0-Level bonus spells. 2= No 0-Level bonus spells.<br>
_<b>Instructions:</b> <font color=darkred>(Default=1)</font>
_ 1= Shows instructions (if called from .Start) 2= To activate the table (if called from .Start)<br>
_<b>Ally4:</b> <font color=darkred>(Default=0)</font> DO NOT MODIFY (only to link with Monster Stats.tab)<br>
_<b>AllyCount4:</b> <font color=darkred>(Default=0)</font> DO NOT MODIFY (only to link with Monster Stats.tab)<br>

